Modules in asnible - yum
 shell
 anible test -m shell -a 'll' 
 service
 ansible test -m service -a 'name=apache2 state=started' -become
 user 
 ping
 setup
 ansible test -m setup  to check setup of a system
 copy 
 ansible test -m copy -a 'src=path/to/src/ dest=/detinstaion/path' -u username
 apt
 ansible test -m apt -a 'name=apache2 state=present' -become -u ishan
 
 
 Variable---
 Variables in asnible are same as linux variables i.e some system valriables and some user defined varioables
 variable can have alphabets, numbers and underscore but it can't start with a number and should not have space and - between
 
 Variables with array
 you can use arrays and assign them to variables
variables with dictionary 

Example of variable
enabling selinux and disabling

---
- name: Enable or disable SELinux
  hosts: test
  vars:
           status: disabled
           tasks: 
           - name: change SELinux config
             lineinfile:
                     path: /etc/selinux/config
                     regexp: '^SELINUX='
                     line: 'SELINUX={{ status }}'
...

We can check sytax of a file through adding --syntax-check at the end

---ANSIBLE TAGS---
we can use tags to skip certain steps in a yml file or can run specific tasks inside yaml file
use "--tags"  to run specific tags
use "--skip-tags" to skip specific tags


----ANSIBLE ROLES--------
DEFAULT-  directory is for defining variable defaults
and it has the lowest priority and If the variables are not defines anywherethen the variable in defaults/main.yml will be used

FILES -  used for adding files

HANDLERS- used for storing handlers

META - use for storing authorship information
